about.description:
sphinx-click is a Sphinx plugin that allows you to automatically extract
documentation from a click-based application and include it in your docs.
about.summary: A Sphinx plugin to automatically document click-based applications

name: sphinx-click
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "sphinx-click" %}
{% set version = "2.1.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9ceb0ee39e9734f39f593f99499e2a2f8e62929ac0b5f040b1d0411c02efaab7

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - pbr >=2.0
  run:
    - python
    - sphinx >=1.5,<2.1

test:
  imports:
    - sphinx_click

about:
  home: https://pypi.org/project/sphinx-click/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A Sphinx plugin to automatically document click-based applications' 
  description: |
    sphinx-click is a Sphinx plugin that allows you to automatically extract 
    documentation from a click-based application and include it in your docs.
  doc_url: https://sphinx-click.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/click-contrib/sphinx-click

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - CurtLH
